Properties.Name: passFailCriteria
Properties.Description: Pass fail criteria for a test.

Type.Name: PassFailCriteria
Type.Description: Pass fail criteria for a test.

Properties.Name: passFailMetrics
Properties.Description: Map of id and pass fail metrics { id  : pass fail metrics }.

Properties.Name: clientMetric
Properties.Description: The client metric on which the criteria should be applied.

Properties.Name: aggregate
Properties.Description:
The aggregation function to be applied on the client metric. Allowed functions
- ‘percentage’ - for error metric , ‘avg’, ‘p50’, ‘p90’, ‘p95’, ‘p99’, ‘min’,
‘max’ - for response_time_ms and latency metric, ‘avg’ - for requests_per_sec,
‘count’ - for requests

Properties.Name: requestName
Properties.Description: Request name for which the Pass fail criteria has to be applied

Properties.Name: value
Properties.Description:
The value to compare with the client metric. Allowed values - ‘error : [0.0 ,
100.0] unit- % ’, response_time_ms and latency : any integer value unit- ms.

Properties.Name: action
Properties.Description: Action taken after the threshold is met. Default is ‘continue’.

Properties.Name: actualValue
Properties.Description: The actual value of the client metric for the test run.

Properties.Name: autoStopCriteria
Properties.Description: Auto stop criteria for a test. This will automatically stop a load test if the error percentage is high for a certain time window.

Type.Name: AutoStopCriteria
Type.Description: Auto stop criteria for a test. This will automatically stop a load test if the error percentage is high for a certain time window.

Properties.Name: autoStopDisabled
Properties.Description: Whether auto-stop should be disabled. The default value is false.

Properties.Name: errorRate
Properties.Description: Threshold percentage of errors on which test run should be automatically stopped. Allowed values are in range of 0.0-100.0

Properties.Name: errorRateTimeWindowInSeconds
Properties.Description: Time window during which the error percentage should be evaluated in seconds.

Properties.Name: secrets
Properties.Description:
Secrets can be stored in an Azure Key Vault or any other secret store. If the
secret is stored in an Azure Key Vault, the value should be the secret
identifier and the type should be AKV_SECRET_URI. If the secret is stored
elsewhere, the secret value should be provided directly and the type should be
SECRET_VALUE.

Properties.Name: value
Properties.Description: The value of the secret for the respective type

Properties.Name: value
Properties.Description: The value of the certificate for respective type

Properties.Name: environmentVariables
Properties.Description: Environment variables which are defined as a set of <name,value> pairs.

Properties.Name: engineInstances
Properties.Description: The number of engine instances to execute load test. Supported values are in range of 1-400. Required for creating a new test.

Properties.Name: splitAllCSVs
Properties.Description:
If false, Azure Load Testing copies and processes your input files unmodified
across all test engine instances. If true, Azure Load Testing splits the CSV
input data evenly across all engine instances. If you provide multiple CSV
files, each file will be split evenly.

Properties.Name: quickStartTest
Properties.Description:
If true, optionalLoadTestConfig is required and JMX script for the load test is
not required to upload.

Properties.Name: endpointUrl
Properties.Description: Test URL. Provide the complete HTTP URL. For example, https://contoso-app.azurewebsites.net/login

Properties.Name: requestsPerSecond
Properties.Description: Target throughput (requests per second). This may not be necessarily achieved. The actual throughput will be lower if the application is not capable of handling it.

Properties.Name: maxResponseTimeInMs
Properties.Description: Maximum response time in milliseconds of the API/endpoint.

Properties.Name: baselineTestRunId
Properties.Description: Id of the test run to be marked as baseline to view trends of client-side metrics from recent test runs

Operations.Name: listTestRuns
Operations.Summary: Get all test runs for the given filters.
Operations.Description: Get all test runs for the given filters.

Parameters.Name: apiVersion
Parameters.Description: The API version to use for this operation.

Parameters.Name: orderby
Parameters.Description:
Sort on the supported fields in (field asc/desc) format. eg: executedDateTime
asc. Supported fields - executedDateTime

Parameters.Name: search
Parameters.Description:
Prefix based, case sensitive search on searchable fields - description,
executedUser. For example, to search for a test run, with description 500 VUs,
the search parameter can be 500.

Parameters.Name: testId
Parameters.Description: Unique name of an existing load test.

Parameters.Name: executionFrom
Parameters.Description: Start DateTime(RFC 3339 literal format) of test-run execution time filter range.

Parameters.Name: executionTo
Parameters.Description: End DateTime(RFC 3339 literal format) of test-run execution time filter range.

Parameters.Name: status
Parameters.Description: Comma separated list of test run status.

Parameters.Name: maxpagesize
Parameters.Description: Number of results in response.
